## Tasks

### 1. Check and Commit Pending Changes

```bash
git status
```

If there are uncommitted changes:
- Stage all changes: `git add -A`
- Commit with message: `chore({{ feature_slug }}): finalize implementation`

### 2. Push Branch

```bash
git push -u origin {{ branch }}
```

### 3. Read Specs for PR Description

Read these files to understand what was implemented:
- `.gba/{{ feature_slug }}/specs/design.md`
- `.gba/{{ feature_slug }}/specs/verification.md`

Also check the diff:
```bash
git diff {{ base_branch }}...HEAD --stat
```

### 4. Create PR with Detailed Description

Use `gh pr create` with a comprehensive description:

```bash
gh pr create --base {{ base_branch }} --head {{ branch }} --title "feat({{ feature_slug }}): <brief title from design>" --body "<detailed body>"
```

The PR body should include:
- **Summary**: Clear description of what was implemented (from design spec)
- **Changes**: Key changes with bullet points
- **Implementation Phases**: List all phases with commit links
- **Testing**: How it was verified (from verification spec)
- **Statistics**: Include the execution statistics table

End the body with:
```
---

🤖 Generated by [GBA](https://github.com/tyrchen/gba) (Geektime Bootcamp Agent)
```

### 5. Output the PR URL

After creating the PR, output ONLY the PR URL on the last line, like:
```
PR_URL: https://github.com/owner/repo/pull/123
```

## IMPORTANT

- Create a well-written, professional PR description
- Include all relevant technical details from the specs
- The PR description should be comprehensive enough for reviewers to understand the changes
- Output the PR URL at the end so it can be captured
